In the Matter of the ENTERPRISE BRASS FOUNDRY, a Corporation, Bankrupt. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 1, 1925.) No. 4258. For opinion below, see 293 F. 69. Thos. P. Revelle, U. S. Atty., and C. T. McKinney, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Seattle, Wash., for appellant. Winter S. Martin and Ray M. War-dall, both of Seattle, Wash., for appellee.

Before HUNT and RUDKIN, Circuit Judges, and BOURQUIN, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Reversed, on authority of In re West Coast Rubber Corporation (C. C. A.) 290 F. 160, affirmed by the Supreme Court under date of April 13, 1925, 45 S. Ct. 386, 69 L. Ed. —. •
